messages.text: Yas! Do you wanna come stay at mine again tomorrow? Mum bought home Ben&Jerrys with our name on…
Of course, it’s a Friday tradition by now right?
And traditions can’t be broken….. ;)
Why would I want to? See you tomorrow :D
two days later
Hey Em! Thanks for having me over last night, I had a great time. I always feel so much more chill at your house…
That’s because your parents are mental :P
Not *that* mental! Just a bit… strict :P
Same thing in my book
Oh come on, they’re not too bad, at least they let me go round yours!
That redeems them slightly I suppose ;)
Do you think they’ll let you go to Matts party next week?
What do you think?
Why not?? You just said they let you come round mine!
Yeahhh, but there are *boys* at the party
I swear they think all boys are monsters just put on earth to attack you :P
Or seduce me….
ahahahhaha can you even imagine Matt being seductive??
That’s what’s so stupid about it! My parents have obviously never met any high school boys :L
Yoyoyoyo yass
Esmie??? It’s 2am what the hell
Just wantd to chat 4$
Omg are you drunk??
Ysss.
Maybe we should talk tomorrow…
nononono
now
I miss you tas
yas
yeah yeah, now get to bed :L
nonono
I really miss u
I thik I love you
Yas????? I sorry
we see each other all the time
and boys ar stupid
right?
a little bit later
Hey Yas, I’m so sorry about what I said last night ☹ I really am. I don’t want to ruin anything.
I thought we were on the same page. But we’re not and it’s cool and we can just go back to normal.
I can believe you could even think that I could even feel that way Esmie??
I’m not even upset about, y’know, you feeling like that. It’s just. I can’t.
My parents won’t even let me go to parties! Can you imagine how they’d react if I started dating a *girl*??
So, it’s just your parents stopping you?
No!
idk
I’ve never thought of us like that. I can’t. It’s too different.
My mum’s got a wedding book ffs.
And you can’t picture me and you in it? Are you being serious?
I… don’t know. It’s too different! I can’t think.
Is this really you?
Fine. It’s fine. Just let me know when you’re done thinking.
a week later
Esmie… hi. I know I’m probably the last person you wanna speak to.
But I wanted to talk to you about something, can we meet tonight?
Yasmin? Hi, this is Esmie’s mom…. Look I’m sorry to break this to you darling, I thought you knew.
I just didn’t think when it happened, and I don’t know, I thought she might have told you. But she’s asleep now.
Tell me what Mrs Janssen? Why do you have Esmie’s phone? Why is she asleep now?
Yasmin, Esmie is really ill, honey. She’s got cancer. We found out only yesterday… It’s leukemia.
The symptoms came on so fast, we didn’t think it could be serious.
But our doctor spotted the pattern straight away, thank god he did.
We’re at the general hospital over on 5th, why don’t you come and visit some time this week? She won’t mind.
Whatever’s happened, I’m sure you can put it behind you.
Oh poor Esmie. I’ll come as soon as I can– today!
a few hours later
Yasmin! Thank you for coming today, it got me through, it really did. I felt so alone in that place.
You’d better get used to it, you know I’m gonna be there every day from now on ;)
There’s something I didn’t tell you today, at the hospital…
I need a bone marrow transplant, but I can’t get one anytime soon….
My family, for some reason, don’t match. My mom always did say I took after my grandmother :P
And there are no donors available?? What does this mean??
No…. I’m not priority. The cancer is not as aggressive as it could be. But, the longer they leave it…
Can I be your donor?
I know it might not be a match, but can I try?
I can’t ask you to do that! I haven’t even thought about it!
I’ll come back and we can ask your doctor. It’s worth a try right? Especially if you get treated quicker….
Anything to spend more time with you.
a few days later
YASMIN IT’S A MATCH. They can give me your bone marrow along with my chemotherapy!
I’ve got a higher chance now than ever before.
Oh I’m so so happy! And I’ll be with you every step of the way, absolutely every single one.
You’re my best friend Yasmin. I’m so lucky to have you.
I can be more than that, Esmie.
What?
I was thinking, when I found out that you were ill, I was so scared.
I was just overcome with fear that I would never see you again…. And, well, life just didn’t seem worth it.
When I say I’ll be with you, I mean it – we can be together properly.
But what about your parents?? I don’t want you to get in trouble. I really don’t.
It doesn’t matter anymore Esmie. If we can beat this illness, we can beat anything together.
I love you, Yas.
I love you too.
P.s. I’m on my way to the hospital, I bought Ben&Jerrys ;)
